# Helper Script and Automation Tools

## Note Creation Script
Location: [scripts/new_note.sh](mdc:scripts/new_note.sh)

### Usage
```bash
./scripts/new_note.sh "Note Title" <category> [slug]
```

### Categories and Aliases
- `ml` or `machine-learning` - Machine Learning notes
- `algo` or `algorithms` - Algorithms & Problem Solving
- `sd`, `system-design`, `system`, or `sys` - System Design

### Examples
```bash
# Default ML category
./scripts/new_note.sh "Neural Networks"

# Explicit category
./scripts/new_note.sh "Binary Search Algorithm" algo

# With custom slug
./scripts/new_note.sh "Load Balancing Strategies" sd load-balancing

# Using aliases
./scripts/new_note.sh "Decision Trees" machine-learning decision-trees
```

## What the Script Does
1. Validates the category (must be ml/algo/sd or their aliases)
2. Generates a slug from the title if not provided
3. Creates the appropriate directory structure if needed
4. Uses the [note template](mdc:templates/note-template.md) to create the file
5. Replaces placeholders (TITLE, DATE, SLUG, CATEGORY)

## Template Placeholders
The template uses these placeholders:
- `{{TITLE}}` - Note title
- `{{DATE}}` - Current date (YYYY-MM-DD)
- `{{SLUG}}` - Generated or provided slug
- `{{CATEGORY}}` - Note category

## File Structure Created
```
notes/
├── ml/
│   └── {slug}.md
├── algo/
│   └── {slug}.md
└── sd/
    └── {slug}.md
```